column5: hi have my 17 1/2 Alumacraft 115 Johnson am in Kinmount area & Norland  area for bass & walleye other then Balsam lake slot limit. good free area to put the boat in the water. second part of my question how deep is Moore lake & gull lake,
so are you looking for good (FREE) boat ramps in that area to put your boat in , but not interested in Balsam because of the slot limit on walleye
The town of Haliburton has a free launch, concrete too I believe.  That gives you access to a chain of 5 lakes and multiple species
to add am driving from Scarborough to the area I mention's. gas prices will play a big part where I want to travel. thanks for the help. this area is new to me.
You may want to move this thread or post it on the general board.  This is the classified section.
if I knew how I would just delete it. my post.

Gull and Moore are rocky, deep, lake trout lakes, Gull max depth is 165', Moore around 100'  bass and walleye, like Fisnsled said, Head/ Grass/ Kash/ Canning chain, free launch on Head and Kash - Beech and Maple lakes in Stanhope, free launch on both -Burnt River, free launch in Kinmount and go north (upstream)  the above lakes , no slot, 1 over 18"  - Head Lake (different Head Lk) on 45, west of Norland (keep them in the slot, unlike Balsam), free launch -Shadow, keepers are in the slot too, launch on Public Launch Road -check out Crystal Lk too
